# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Git distributes the APPARATUS. Obsidian Sync distributes the CONTENT.
# So the repo stays empty of threads/records — they live in Obsidian Sync.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# content — synced via Obsidian, never committed (keep the seed thread + record store).
# Thread VIEWS live flat in notes/; the immutable CARDS live under _system/records/.
notes/*
!notes/main.md
_system/records/*
!_system/records/.gitkeep

# local daemon + runtime state (per-machine; must NOT sync either)
.stream/

# secrets — keys never go in the vault (backstop; real location is ~/.config/exo/.env)
.env
.env.*
*.key
*.pem
secrets/

# python
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc

# obsidian per-machine UI state
.obsidian/workspace.json
.obsidian/workspace-mobile.json

# os
.DS_Store

# Note: DASHBOARD.md is tracked (it ships as the empty-state status view) but it
# regenerates locally on every action — local modifications to it are expected
# and need not be committed.
